JD 25-
-This is a great opportunity to manage the centralisation of all learning content at scale to provide a single source of truth for all IHG learning content
-You will join the Global Learning Effectiveness (GLE) team comprising of the Director, 2 Global Learning Analytics Insights Managers and Consultant Analysts
-The GLE team sit within the Global Learning Strategy and Effectiveness Centre of Excellence
-Manage the centralisation of all learning content by developing a content management architecture (permissions, folders, 
 metadata list classifications and tagging) that will ensure the Learning Content Management System (LCMS) provides one single source
 of truth for all IHG learning content.
-Develop a learning content management strategy, based on best practice, to support and evolve the IHG learning ecosystem.
-Chair the Learning Content Management Governance Committee and define the maintenance process for evaluating governance across the platform.
-Create and maintain standards, policies and processes that govern the use of the LCM platform (Xyleme).
-Create, communicate and maintain content management and work execution processes, providing support to LCMS users, liaising with
 Global Learning Applied Technology teams and Global Design Development teams to ensure content is published and delivered quickly and consistently, 
 version control maintained and IHG IP protected.
-Manage the accuracy and consistency of content across all learning platforms by providing content governance at the component level and
 a management process for updating content changes as they occur.
-Managing user security permissions for content tools (ADOBE and Syndicate), applying restrictions to sensitive processes/procedures.
-Manage and deliver LCMS reporting and analytics to provide an accurate and objective picture of our content engagement, consumption, 
 performance and user satisfaction.
-Lead on guidance to content owners/developers to maximise evergreen content and re-purpose and re-utilise content.
-Build out LCM as part of the IHG University ecosystem.
-Stay up to date on emerging trends and technologies within field and adjacent to field and identify and apply as appropriate best practices.
-Discover, assess, recommend, and implement platforms and tools to enhance our ability to deliver best-in-class content capabilities.
-Work with stakeholders to develop and launch new content and functionality, and measure results for continuous improvement.
-Develop into a subject matter expert in one or more areas of analytics/content management.
-Provide input into content management systems and content maintenance.
-Lead on dissemination of collected data in a manner that facilitates appropriate decision making for stakeholders.
-Coordinate/provide training to any new users.
-Manage the licensing agreement.
-Respond to technical support questions (tier 1 support, escalate to Xyleme).
-Bachelors or Masters Degree in Marketing, Advertising, Digital, Business, or a relevant field of work, or an equivalent combination
 of education and work-related experience.
